.DT
pick_al
Disk World creator help
pick_al

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
pick_al -  This function produces a random alignment for an npc, based on a normal distribution around a supplied average, with a maximum and minimum limit provided by a requested range.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int pick_al(int average,
int range)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^average%^RESET%^ - The average alignment for this npc
%^BOLD%^range%^RESET%^ - The range request for alignment - the difference between
average and maximum possible alignment
<p>

.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/obj/handlers/hospital.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This function produces a random alignment for an npc, based on a
normal distribution around a supplied average, with a maximum and
minimum limit provided by a requested range.


The alignment produced will be within the range[ average - range, average + range ]
.EP

